        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 9 at 1:27PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 127 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 22
miles east of Amalia, or 35 miles west of Raton, moving south at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vermejo Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
